short of a length, outside off stump and Smith blocks it, India make a superb start to Pro20, a dot ball!
and Smith tucks it off his hips for his first run of the series, he'll be a relieved man, Zaheer hasn't found the swing into the left-hander in his first two balls
pitches outside off and moves wider from Loots Bosman, that's too wide
identical ball, but a touch closer to the batsman and this time it's a legal ball
the ball whirrs past the outside edge, that pitched on off and moved a shade away, Bosman drove at it and was beaten
and again, moving across the right-hander from over the wicket, Bosman wafts and misses
played to point, loud calls of "No!" from the batsman, Zaheer starts superbly conceding just 2 off the first over
not your typical Pro20 pitch this, that pitched on Smith's off stump and moved away from the left-hander, Smith played and missed
and this one pitches outside off, Smith lets it go and after it passes him it moves back towards Dhoni
whoops, Sreesanth did a Harmison! That was so wide that it went between first and second slip for four wides, the pressure's off South Africa
dropped short and wide, Smith crashes that through covers for the first boundary off the bat
driven to mid-on off the front foot
poor ball, too full from Sreesanth and Smith plays a delightful straight drive past mid-off for four, his regaining his touch
driven slightly uppishly to cover
dabbed to point for a sharp single, Kaif screams in, picks up and shies at the non-striker's end but misses
short of a length outside off stump, Smith moves across and drops it short of midwicket for a single
fuller in length and outside off, Bosman throws everything behind it and slashes it to third man
angling into Smith's middle and leg stump from over the wicket, defended on the leg side on the back foot
again Zaheer keeps it outside off, once again Smith walks across his stumps and works it off his pads to fine leg
Bosman goes, tame edge to Tendulkar at first slip, Zaheer kept it full outside off, taking the ball away from the right hander, Bosman drove at it and only managed to get the edge
full and wide outside off, Smith lets that go
whoops, that had Smith in a tangle, the seam was upright, it pitched outside off, Smith moved across again and the ball beat the outside edge
and again, how close was that to the outside edge, Smith drives again outside off and the away movement beats him
another big big wide outside off, Sreesanth just needs to keep his cool here, he's beaten Smith with consecutive balls, he doesn't want to release the pressure with wides
much straighter and short of a length, Smith defends on the back foot
whack, what a shot that was, premeditated perhaps, for Smith was down the track in a trice and bashed Sreesanth's short-of-a-length ball over mid-off
fuller ball on the pads, Smith whips it to mid-on
Gibbs gets a ripper first up, Zaheer pitches that on a perfect length and moves it away from the right-hander. Gibbs gets squared up and the ball zips past the edge
a touch shorter outside off, Gibbs gets forward and defends to point
loud appeal for lbw, Zaheer thought he had a good case - as all bowlers do - but that pitched outside leg and was too high

it's mayhem out there, Gibbs drives to cover, Mongia dives superbly to stop it, Karthik picks up the ball, Smith is in big trouble running towards the striker's end, Karthik shies, he misses and concedes overthrows
a touch short, not that short mind you and Gibbs short-arm pulls it over midwicket for four
he strikes first ball, perhaps a trifle lucky because it was very wide and was moving wider away from Gibbs who plonked his front foot down and bashed it straight at Raina at cover
left alone outside off
in the channel outside off and Kemp lets it go again
a shade straighter and on a good length, Kemp moves forward and defends
that pitched short of a length and cut back very sharply into Kemp, that ball hit him high on the thigh
tight line, tight length, defended on the leg side, Agarkar starts with a maiden wicket in Pro20
short of a length outside off, defended on the front foot
that's a shocking wide from Zaheer
angling into Smith from over the wicket, worked of the pads behind square
pitches on off stump and moves away from the right-hander, Kemp lets it go
punched through cover
full and straight, Smith tries to charge and whack it down the ground but gets inside edge to midwicket

and Zaheer underlines the fact that Smith is his bunny. Full ball angling into the left-hander, Smith moves a shade across and gets hit on the back pad plumb in front, that's four out of four for Zaheer against Smith
defended to point on the back foot
short of a length on middle and leg, tucked off the pads on the leg side
short and wide outside off, de Villiers slashes at it but doesn't make contact
short_text: Agarkar to de Villiers, no run

text: take that! Agarkar dishes up a short and wie ball, AB de Villiers frees his arms and slaps that over third man, super six
that bounced on de Villiers just outside of stump, he lets it go
short_text: Agarkar to de Villiers, no run

text: got him, Agarkar has two in two overs. He serves that full and swinging away from the right-hander, de Villiers drives ahrd at it, gets the edge and Dhoni  takes a low catch
poor start, short and wide, bashed through cover for four
straighter ball on midle stump, defended on the leg side
short ball, Kemp tries to pull and gloves it over Dhoni for four more, More dancing in the stands, more music and much fun
good length ball outside off, defended on the off side
fuller ball, swingign back into the right hander, Kemp plays forward and gets an inside edge on to the pad
superb bowling, this one pitches on the ideal length adn shapes away from Kemp who gets squared up and beaten
an appeal for lbw is turned down, that pitched outside leg and hit Morkel on the pad
played through cover point for a single, South Africa bring up their fifty at less than 6 runs per over

short of a length outside off, Kemp majestically stands up tall and punches through cover, the ball races to the fence and quicksilver Karthik dives superbly on the fence to save the four, he has a little trouble in spottign the ball after he saved it but a superb efort nevertheless
short and drifting down leg side, Kemp works it past square leg to the fence, easy pickings
straighter line and better length, worked on the leg side for one
fired in outside the off, Morkel slashes and misses
full outside off stump, moving away, Kemp has an almighty heave and fails to male contact
full on the stumps, Kemp comes forward and drives past Pathan's outstretched left hand and picks up two down the ground
fullish on off stump, Kemp comes forward and ends up defending, well bowled
short this time, Kemp quickly swivels and pulls out to Tendulkar on the deep midwicket, who fumbles the take
short and wide, some movement into him, but he stands and steers that down to Sreesanth at third man for the single
full and swinging into leg stump, Kemp flicks that down to Sreesanth at deep fine leg and retains the strike
short outside off stump, carved through the off side to Kaif on the deep cover ropes
slower ball, teasingly on the stumps and Morkel defends back to Tendulkar
quicker on middle and off, pushed to point, no run however
wobbles this one on off stump, this time Morkel picks up one in front of point

spins this one quicker outside off stump, van der Wath has a flirt but cant make contact, good over from Tendulkar

full on leg stump, he swings and misses, ball hits the leg
full outside off stump, Morkel has a good old agricultural heave across the line and times that in the gap at midwicket and picks up four, a welcome one
oh ho! Dropped in short, Morkel simply flat-bats that over mid-wicket for maximum
short outside off stump, and its chopped into the covers for one
full and swinging away outside off stump, he drives airily and gets a thick outside edge down to third man

text: full in the zone, a yorker, well bowled and well dug out

text: short and moving into him outside off stump, batsman swings across the line but connects with the chilly air, thats it, a dot ball!

text: and again, short and moving into him, he swings at it but gets hit on the chest...ouch...

short_text: Sreesanth to van der Wath, 1 leg bye

text: short and slightly wide, crunched to point and thats well stopped
huge! Too short, too wide, and Morkel hops in the air and uppercuts that fiercly over the point fence, crowd goes berzerk! What a hit!
tossed up on the stumps, defended to cover

short_text: Harbhajan Singh to van der Wath, 1 run

flatter and quicker, in the blockhole, dug out to the on side

text: short and its pulled past square leg for one
short_text: Sreesanth to van der Wath, 1 run

good length ball on the stumps, he whips that to mid-wicket
short_text: Sreesanth to van der Wath, no run

text: full on middle and leg, easily whipped through mid-wicket for a couple

flat and quick on the stumps, thumped over Harbhajan to the man at long-off

tossed up again, and its driven into the covers
well bowled! Full in the blockhole, dug out back to Pathan, useful stuff
short and wide, quick ball that swings back into him but he's backed away too far and misses out on the flashy uppercut, a dot ball
full outside off stump, driven down to Tendulkar at long-off, a run, finally!
full outside off stump, driven out to Kaif on the deep extra cover ropes, ones coming now, but no fours

lands on a good length outside off stump, van der Wath swings that across the line and down to wide long-on for two

text: tossed up outside off stump, quicker, smashed down to long-off
quicker in the blockhole, no room to drive, van der Wath backs away and squeezes that past point

a full toss, van der Wath charges and slams that over mid-on, and Raina makes a good stop on the ropes

text: he oversteps! Was a good ball, cramped him for room, flicked to backward square leg, a free hit coming up
short_text: Harbhajan Singh to van der Wath, (no ball) 1 run

text: madness! Flat outside off stump, and he slogs the free hit down to the man at long-on, who takes the catch, but Peterson's lost his marbles, and begins to walk away, thinking he was out, and the throw that comes back to Harbhajan is whipped off with the bails, and Peterson has to go...oh ho!
gone! Tossed up outside off stump, and its slogged down Raina's throat at long-on, Harbhajan gets him! Thats two in two for India...
short_text: Harbhajan Singh to van der Wath, OUT

text: flat on the stumps, slogged to mid-wicket
full in the zone, slogged down to fine leg with the inside edge
well bowled, slower into the legs, and he cant time the flick
tossed up on off stump, worked to backward point where the throw comes in a flash, Dhoni whips off the stumps and he's gone!
lands just outside off stump, he walks across the stumps and gets rapped on the pads, not out says the umpire
tossed up, slammed down to long-off and they run hard, two is always on the cards and the throw is off, and thats the end of South Africa's innings
Sehwag cops a body blow first up, van der Wath bangs it short and angles that into Segwag's mid-riff

text: juicy delivery that, full and wide outside off, Sehwag gets on the front foot and slaps it through cover for four, India are on the board

text: smashed hard to cover where a superb save cuts off the boundary
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

text: short of a length outside off stump, Sehwag drives hard but straight to point
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

short of a length and on middle stump, Tendulkar moves across again and tucks it off his pads
loud loud shout for lbw, Umpire Jerling said not out, that pitched on off and cut back into Tendulkar who got across his stumps and got hit a touch high on the pad
full outside off, Tendulkar gets half forward and pushes it to cover
what was that? A mis-field from a South African? That's like spotting a Dodo in this age. Tendulkar pushed that to mid-off where Morkel;s fumble allowed the single
beaten by one that pitched outside off and moved away from Tendulkar's fishing blade
Tendulkar plays it to point, Langeveldt overstepped, free hit coming up
Tendulkar tries to slog it out of the ground, gets a thick edge to Boucher who takes the catch but the batsman can't be out off a free hit
beaten outside the off stump
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

text: nearly chopped it on! van der Wath brought that back into Sehwag who tried to cut but got a thick bottom edge past the stumps
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

text: Was that Superman? de Villiers defies gravity to take that wide ball down leg side, splendid save
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, 1 wide

short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

text: pitches outside off stumpa nd swings away from Sehwag who ... lets it go
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, no run

text: sublime shot, full outside off, Tendulkar gets on the front foot and drives that perfectly between cover and mid-off for four
much better length from Langeveldt, Tendulkar goes back and defends to point
Tendulkar's taking Langeveldt on now, that was full and very wide, Tendulkar tries to flay it over extra cover but slices it behind point for four
angling into the pads from over the wicket, defended on the leg side
Langeveldt gets his man, Tendulkar tried to smash one from outside off, he tried to hit it too hard and chopped it on to his stumps, the crowds explode in celebration
pitches on leg and hits Mongia on the pad
you can't bowl on the pads to Sehwag, he easily flicked that behind square for four
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, FOUR

text: excellent length and it jags back into Sehwag from off stump, Sehwag gets hit on the pad and they run a leg bye to point
short_text: van der Wath to Sehwag, 1 leg bye

text: hits the good length straightaway, worked down to third man for one
banged over midwicket for four, Telemachus dropped that far too short, Mongia got into position in a flash and lofted for a one-bounce four
wafts again outside the off stump at one that moves away from him, gets beaten
much closer to the stumps and once again Mongia fends for it outside off and gets beaten
short of a length and on middle and leg, Mongia gets on the back foot and defends on the legside
he doesn't have much of a clue about balls that pitch just outside off nad move away from him, that's the umpteenth time he's been beaten by such a ball
straight line and just short of a length, hits Sehwag on the pad
defended on the leg side

short and wide outside off and it bounces on Sehwag who, predictably, upper cuts it, Roger Telemauchus runs across, the balls movign away from him, he gets two hands to it as he dives towards the fence but the ball bounces into his hands and over the fence
width offered outside off and Sehwag guides that past first slip and down to the third man fence
dropped short of cover on the front foot for a quick single
short of a length, pitches on leg, Mongia moves across and tries to flick but is extremely early on the shot, gets a leading edge towards cover
supreme one-day, oops, Pro20 shot, not that short and not that wide but Sehwag cuts that fine down to the third man fence
width ofered again outside off, Sehwag cuts past point
Telemachus bounces Sehwag who doesn't quite manage to get out of the way, the ball hits the helmet and runs down to fine leg for four leg byes
defended on the leg side, they thought about the single but wisely decided against it
that's terribly wide, poor ball, Sehwag has a go at it but can't reach it, wide called
Telemachus comes back well, angles that into Sehwag's middle stump, tucked to midwicket for a single
angles across the left hander from over teh wciket, defended to point
full on the pads, Sehwag flicks it off his pads and times it well enough to run two
short ball, Sehwag backs away and cuts hard over point, that went like a tracer bullet to the fence
oooh he needs to keep his cool here, he backs away again and tries to heave it over the off side but misses
angling into Sehwag from over the wicket, cramping him for room, defended to point for one
perfect length and line to Mongia, pitching on off and moving away from the left hander, Mongia fended at it from his crease and was beaten
pushed into the covers for  s single to end the over
and Mongia gets beaten again outside the off stump, this is getting very predictable now, he can't touch one in that area
width offered this time outside off, Mongia frees his arms to cut but missed that by a long way

disaster for India! Sehwag is run-out. Mongia drives it to mid-off and sets off for the run, Sehwag takes off from the non-striker's end, Mongia changes his mind and turns back, Sehwag is left stranded more than half-way down, the throw from mid-off is a poor one but Langeveldt collects it and dives full length to break the stumps, memories of Jonty Rhodes from the 1992 World Cup come to mind
full on the pads, Mongia flicks that easily through midwicket for four
width offered from outside off, guided down to third man for one
left alone outside off stump
full on the stumps, Mongia tucks that around the corner and runs hard, he wants two and gets it in the end, well run
lands on a good length on middle and leg, Mongia defends back towards the bowler
one bounce and four! Gives him the charge and slams that cleanly over mid-on with a flow of the arms, welcome boundary for India
full and moving across him, he gets forward and drops the hands on it, calls of 'NO' back to Dhoni as Gibbs swoops in from point

insane! A good, full delivery on off stump, Mongia defends and his bat brakes cleanly in half! I've never seen that happen before! Wasn't even an express delivery, or Brett Lee bowling, but the ball landed smack on the maker's name and spliced it in half! SG sponsors must be hiding their faces...
good length ball on the stumps, he defends...his bats in one piece, all good

Langeveldt! A quick, good length ball outside off stump, Dhoni stands there and tries some sort of late cut/dab and succeeds in chopping onto his off stump...no fireworks from him, South Africa on top!
full ball going down leg, Karthick falls over trying to flick, sets off for the run and runs smack into Langeveldt
quick and again pitched outside leg stump, raps Mongia on the leg, and thats some appeal from the bowler, not out says the umpire
dropped in short on middle and leg, he hops and swivels  that down past square leg, Bosman on the ropes covers good ground, slides, and saves four
lands on off stump and moves it in to Mongia, who stands leaden-footed and almost chops onto his stumps, but the ball sneaks past middle and off...whew!
beauty, sir, beauty! Lands this on a sweet spot outside off stump, and the swing beats a stiff Karthik, who stands and feels for that and is clueless, good over from Langeveldt
fullish on middle and leg, driven loosely to midwicket
lands this outside off stump and shaves it away, and for the zillionth time Mongia just stands and plays away from his body
this one's straighter and now Mongia manages to work it in the gap at mid-wicket for one
full outside off stump, onto the front foot comes Karthik, pushing to point for one
a good length outside off stump, Mongia backs away and drives to cover, who fields and saves runs
oh, a four! Fullish on off stump, Mongia charges down the track and swings that across the line, manages to find the gap between mid-on and mid-wicket and the ball trickles over the ropes
full outside off stump, he drives and gets an inside edge
full outside off stump, driven well but straight to Kemp at cover, Mongia cant beat the gap
full again, and he drives that to Gibbs at point, pressure, pressure...
Mongia awakens! Full outside off stump, Mongia has a step back and just smokes that handsomely over extra cover for a huge six, massive!
middle and leg line, worked into the gap at mid-wicket
fullish outside off stump, little movement, and whats this? Karthik shoulders arms! Hasnt he got the memo? The Tests dont start till a little later this month
a good length outside off stump, steered in the gap at gully down to third man for one
full outside off stump, Karthik comes forward and pushes that to backward point, a dot ball again
quicker on a good length outside off stump, that ball jags in and catches Karthik going nowhere, an inside edge but that speedy de Villiers pulls off a fine diving stop
full on middle and off, and Karthik slams that over mid-on with a shimmy of the feet, times it well and gets four
fullish outside off stump, pushed to Gibbs at backward point
full outside off stump, pitches and swings the other way, and Karthik, swinging wildly, gets beaten all ends up
short and wide, chopped weakly down to third man for one

strives for the yorker, too full and Karthik drives, gets the toe edge of the bat, ball pops down onto the ground and then bobs up to Kemp at slip, who claims the catch as he thought it was off the boot, but after going upstairs its ruled not-out, it was a bump-ball
full outside off stump and moving away, and again Karthik shoulders arms...umm, run rate....??
short and moving into him from outside off stump, and he runs that down to third man for one
short outside off stump, Mongia backs away and frees the arms, doesnt time it well but gets one in the gap at cover
full on middle and off, driven to mid-on who fumbles and allows the run
lands outside off stump, Karthik moves across and cheekily chips that over short fine leg, effective shot
full in the blockhole, Karthik digs that out to cover and calls for the run, good throw from Peterson but he's safe
lands outside off stump and moves in, Mongia picks that from middle stump and chops it down to third man
short and wide, runs it down to third man for one more
full on off stump, pushed into the covers for a quick run
full outside off stump, Karthik slashes that past Gibbs at backward point, who manages to get a hand to it and slow the pace, and the sweeper saves it on the ropes

tossed up, spinning away from him on off stump, Mongia sweeps across the line but misses, and de Villiers whips off the bails in a flash, Mongia's backfoot is on the line, but after what seemed like ages the third umpire rules it not out! He's mad! Mongia was out! Whoah!
tossed up outside off stump, Mongia reverse sweeps but misses, de Villiers takes it

now he's gone! Tossed up on middle and off, Mongia steps out and tries to clear the infield but mistimes the lofted chip and Langeveldt, covering good ground at mid-on, tumbles and holds a great catch
tossed up on the stumps, swept out to deep backward square leg
flat and quick outside off stump, driven to mid-on
quicker and shorter, Karthik advances and tries to work that through mid-wicket, the balls too quick and hurries onto him, he misses the swipe and picks up a leg bye to point
short and wide, Karthik stands and dabs that cheekily past a diving de Villiers and even Henderson diving on the ropes cant prevent the four

text: full outside off stump, Karthik backs away and chops that to point for one, he exposed all the stumps there

short_text: van der Wath to Karthik, no run

text: quick and short, moving into him, he works that off the hips past square leg and settles for one

flatter outside off stump, he tries to sweep but misses...dot ball...
flat and quick on middle and leg, flicked through midwicket...just the single...
flat on middle and off, Raina sweeps past square leg for one, and the match it tied!
full and flat outside off stump, Karthik chops that past backward point to win the match! India have won their first match on tour in tense style, well played!
full and wide down the leg side, McCullum looks to flick but the ball clips the pads and escapes for four leg byes

text: good ball, full and swinging in from outside off stump, Fleming stands leaden-footed and pushes at it, and gets beaten

text: fullish length, McCullum comes down the track to greet the ball, but can only smash that to cover
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: hello and welcome, says Fleming! Full and wide outside off stump, and he just slams that ever so sweetly through the covers, full swing of the arms and thumped for four
four more! Not as full but still very wide, and Fleming has another swing at that, but gets a thick outside edge that flies in the vacant slip region for four

oh ho, another! Maharoof moves around the wicket, and still pitches wide of off stump, and again Fleming  just swings the bat and it and gets a regulation thick edge that screams into that gap at slip and races away for four
a good length outside off stump, Fleming stands and opens the face of the bat to run it down to third man for one
a good length and moving down leg stump, and McCullum times that nicely off the hips, finds the gap behind square, and picks up four more
quicker ball, fullish but going down leg stump, McCullum tries to work it fine but misses, gets rapped on the pads, Maharoof yells in vain but that was clearly going down
a good length on off stump, he looks to smash across the line but cant beat the fielders on the on side
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: a tad fuller, again he looks to swipe across the line, but ends up getting a single towards mid-off
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: good length angled across him, he tries to dab that down to third man but cant beat gully
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: full on middle and leg, driven to mid-on for one
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: full on leg stump, flicked right to short fine leg

text: full outside off stump, the rank half-volley, and McCullum clears the front leg and smokes that nicely over mid-off for four, shot!
full outside off stump again, and this time he swings across the line and ends up mistiming that to midwicket
easy as they come! A full toss on leg stump, and Fleming dispatches that over square leg for four, runs coming hard and fast here!
slower ball, rolls his fingers over it and doesnt pitch it full outside off stump, Fleming is beaten by the slowness and swings wildly and gets beaten
fullish on leg stump, Fleming flicks into square leg and calls for the run, McCullum is in his happy zone and doesnt respond well, theres a mix-up but they get the run, just

he's not dealing in singles! Full toss on middle and leg, and McCullum swivels into his pull shot, not timed well but theres enough power on it to help it along its away over backward square leg for six
fullish, he drives and gets an inside edge to short fine leg
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: full and slow outside off stump, he backs away and tries the dab, but gets beaten

text: shot! Full outside off stump, and he eases into a nice drive past mid-off for four

text: full outside off stump, inside edges the attempted slog into midwicket

superb! Short and wide outside off stump, and its slammed, hard and flat, smack over point for four, Murali at point tried to go for the catch and almost cops one hard on the finger as he tried to get the hand out of the way at the last minute
short of a good length on middle and off, Fleming swings that one-handed over square leg for one
slower and full, the attempted yorker, well bowled, and McCullum does well to dig it out back to Fernando
well bowled! Quick on a good length, angled into the ribs from off stump, and McCullum is cramped for room and ends up defending into the on side
fullish outside off stump, driven out towards mid-off, just a single
Wow! Tossed up outside off stump, and McCullum plants the foot forward and slams that high over long-on for six, welcome Murali!
carnage! A full toss on middle and leg, and McCullum just swings that high over backward square leg for six more
flat outside off stump, McCullum comes forward and uses the soft hands to push it into the covers for one
flat outside off stump, Fleming comes forward and uses the soft hands to push it into the covers for one

bowled 'em! Slower ball on a good length on middle and off, Fleming doesnt expect it to come on that slowly, swings across the line and gets beaten all ends up and his furniture is disturbed! Maharoof gets the crucial breakthrough, but what a start from New Zealand
good ball, full outside off stump and swinging in, Franklin gets half-forward and pokes at it, and gets beaten
back of a good length outside off stump, Franklin comes forward and pushes, getting a thick edge down to Vaas at third man
slower and fullish on leg stump, McCullum works it to square leg for one
good stuff! Slower and fuller outside off stump, Franklin swings across the line and gets beaten comprehensively, a very good over from Maharoof

and he's gone! Tossed up outside off stump, McCullum sweeps from where it landed and can only slog it out to Tharanga at deep midwicket, who pouches a simple catch into his lap, Murali gets his revenge
tossed up outside leg stump, Franklin sweeps to backward square leg
quicker and flatter outside off stump, Taylor cant adjust well enough and ends up dropping the hands, and the ball runs past Sangakkara
tossed up on middle and leg, he sweeps but cant time it at all
again he tosses it up on middle and leg, and this time he times the sweep well enough and picks up four through square leg
full outside off stump, driven down to long-off for one
a good length outside off stump, Franklin drops the hands but cant beat point
fullish on middle and leg, Franklin hits through the line and beats mid-on for four
shot! A good length outside off stump, and Franklin just picks it high over long-off for six, timed sweetly off the middle of the bat, excellent shot
short outside off stump, dabbed to backward point for one
short delivery outside leg, Franklin goes down the legside and tries to pul it, misses teh line and almost drags it back ontoi his stumps
another legside delivery, worked away to the legside for a single
pitches on middle ad straightens, the batsman tries to sweep it, misses and is rapped on the pad, there's a huge appeal from Murali, but the umpire is not interested
comes off the pad and rolls away to the leg side
swept away backward of square for one, doesn't get it off the middle of the bat, but its still runs
wide delivery down the legside, its a straighter one too, Sangakara does well to get a hand to it, but its still to wide and the batsmen cross over for another extra
tossed up delivery, the attempted sweep shot, comes off the inside edge and rolls away to fine leg, the fielder inspite of being inside the 30-yard circle cant save the single though
flat delivery outside the leg stump, driven back past the bowler to mid-on, Jayasuriya rus across and fields it

there's the wicket, well almost!! Jayasuriya throws this one up just a tad, the batsman attempts a sweep shot ad misses the ball completely, looks like he loses balance in teh process and Sangakkara is quick to whip off the bails, its referred to the TV Umpire, but the foots back in time
single to mid wicket
and now there's the wicket!!! its a flat delivery, fired in, Franklin tries his hand at the reverse sweep, misses the ball and is rapped in front - LBWs dont come any easier for the umpires!
fuller delivery outside leg, almost yorker length and its worked away to fine leg for a single - gets off the mark immediately
tossed up this time, the batsman goes for the heave, but misses the ball completely and it comes off his body.
starts off with a regulation good length delivery thats tapped to extra cover for one
fuller length delivery, its guided wide of the man at point, and they scamper through for two - Vaas the fielder there - should have been down to one run there
fuller length and it gets the treatment it deserves, its creamed away through the vacant spaces in the cover region and the ball races away - classy shot that one
its short this time, and this one gets punished rightly, pulled away to the mid wicket fence
nearly a yorker length delivery at 144kmph, its driven away to long on for a brace, took a chance on Atapattu's weak arm then
fuller length again, right up at the batsman's foot, its dug out rightly and they take a single before the mid-on fielder can clean it up
single taken backward of square
again driven to long on and they scamper through for two, Fernando fires in a throw to no-man's land, that's an opportunity for an extra run - two becomes three
again driven to Fernando at long on for one
tossed up delivery, its worked away to mid wicket - the batsmen cross through for a single before Jayawardene can field and return the ball back to the bowler
Murali back, its swept away from in front of the stumps to fine leg, comes off the inside edge of the bat this time

slog sweep this time, misses the ball and is rapped on the pads, huge appeal from Murali, but Sangakkara was clearly down the leg side and that was a good indication to the umpire that it would have missed the leg stump

and again, but this time its out! goes for a slog sweep, misses the ball again, the difference this time is he is hit in front of the off stump, and the umpire reckons it would have crashed into ths stumps. That's out!
tossed up delivery, the batsman comes forward and defends, thinks off a single, takes a start but decides against it
an appeal again, came forward to play a shot - was the bat hidden the pad - not sure, there's an appeal for LBW, but the impact was outside off, and they scamper through for a legbye
tossed up delivery outside off, driven to deep cover for one
tossed up delivery, makes room and tries to cut it, the ball comes off the inside edge
fired down the leg side, Marshall goes for a sweep but doesnt make contact, that was a hit-me kind of a delivery
cut away to deep cover for one

and thats another wicket. tossed up delivery, its driven off the backfoot, comes off the inner half, its spooned up in the air at mid wicket, Chamara Silva times his jump to perfection, can't get it the first time, but grabs it on the second attempt. That's another NZ batsman walking back
starts off with a short delivery, and its pulled away to deep squareleg for one, thats good work by Kapugedera there
bowler_full_name: Denagamage Proboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene

text: reverse swept to thirdman for one, and that's McGlashan's first run in international cricket
bowler_full_name: Denagamage Proboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene
Denagamage Proboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene
Denagamage Proboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene

text: goes for a heave, across the line, but mises the line completely, and the ball goes through to the wicketkeeper betwee the bat and the stumps
bowler_full_name: Denagamage Proboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene

text: slower delivery, and that's a single taken to cover - off the last ball of the over
bowler_full_name: Denagamage Proboth Mahela de Silva Jayawardene

text: tossed up again, and McGlashan tries his hand at the sweep shot, doesn't time it well - all he gets is a single for that much effort
Astle gets max for this one!! its flat this time, and Astle picks the length and the pace, and pulls it away - it was six from the moment it left the bat - good shot then

and now Jayasuriya gets his revenge, its fired in on leg stump and Astle tries the same shot as the previous ball, misses the line and the ball crashes into leg stump - sound of timber as they say, and Astle's short innings comes to an end
Chamara Silva in to the attack now, bowling his leg breaks, its pushed away into the open spaces on the onside for one
tossed up and its cut away to deep point for one, Vaas the man there
short delivery then, goes back to cut it but the ball comes off the bottom edge and Silva fields on his follow through, good work there by the bowler
driven uppishly past the diving bowler for one, spectacular dive by Silva then, but the ball was nowhere close to him

cross batted heave again, McGlashan misses the ball and loses balance, steps out and is found wanting by some quick glovework from Sangakkara who gathers the ball neatly and whips off the bails - no need to refer it to the TV Umpire there, its out!
its a low full toss and its chipped away uppishly to long on, Fernando runs across and pulls it back just in front of the boundary - enough time for two runs there
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: fuller length again, worked away to the mid wicket region for a single
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: swishes outside the off stump and misses, neatly gathered by Sangakkara who is standing upto the stumps
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: you miss I hit! change in pace from Vaas, rolls his fingers over the ball, bowls it full and straight, Bond tries to make room and hit it to the offside, misses it and the ball hits the base of the middle stump
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

text: full length delivery on the stumps, Mark Gillespie gets his foot outisde the off stump and kind of paddle sweeps to the leg side, its hit in the air but there's no man there and there's enough time for a couple
bowler_full_name: Warnakulasuriya Patabendige Ushantha Joseph Chaminda Vaas

quicker and moving high and away from outside off stump, rapped on the pads and they steal a leg bye in front of point

short again on the stumps, not a very quick ball, and Jayasuriya short-arm jabs that nicely over square leg for four, good shot
changes the pace and serves it up a little fuller outside off stump, the ball stays low too and Jayasuriya cant time the cut well at all, misses it
a good length outside off stump, not very quick, and its jabbed to point
full and slow outside off stump, Tharanga stands and just swings the bat at it, missing it all ends up, good start from Franklin
short and wide outside off stump, Tharanga comes down the track, frees the arms, and drives past point out to the deep cover sweeper
thats a wide, too far from Jayasuriya's reach, a freebie
too much width and he cashes in with a nice cut-jab, just dropping the hands on it and placing it in the gap at gully, theres no third man and thats four
too full outside off stump, and Jayasuriya drives that nicely in the gap between cover and mid-off for four more, well done
full on off stump, and he swings that superbly through midwicket or four more, thats three in a row
full outside off stump, he swings the bat at it but fails to make contact
dropped! Fleming placed the short third man for just this chance, and he puts it down! Short and wide, he cuts hard but Franklin lets it through his hands, just in and out, poor stuff
good length delivery angling across outside off, goes after it and misses&
too full and wide outside off stump, he cant even get bat to it, and wide is called, duly
quick on a good length just outside off stump, Jayasuriya pokes at it and gets beaten
slower and fuller outside off stump, Jayasuriya pokes at it and gets an inside edge to leg stump and calls for the run, and it slow getting to the other end and just beats the throw
pitched up outside off, Tharanga drives it to widish mid-off for an easy single
short and wide, slammed over backward point for four
a good length outside off stump, Tharanga slams it out to Ross Taylor on the ropes, who dives well and fields it
comes down the track and goes for the slog, completely misses it
fullish outside off stump, he comes down and slogs it to mid-on
full and wide, slammed high over point for a couple as the ball lands safely
slower delivery, on the legs, Jayasuriya goes for the slof sweep, off the pads to point
good delivery on the stumps, Jayasuriya defends it to mid off
gone! Short and wide, and all he can do is slash it straight to Fleming at a wide gully, who puts the hands up and takes it above his head

dropped! Short and wide, he frees the arms and slashes it over gully, the balls in the air for some time and Taylor moves across from deep cover and cant take it cleanly, the ball was dying on him but he shoudve held onto it, tough but still a chance

driven to mid on

back of a length delivery angling into the right hander, Dilshan plays and misses

fuller length delivery outside  offstump, Silva opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
short of length delivery outside off stump, Dilshan takes a long look and lets it go
good length delivery outside off stump, Dilshan waits for it and shoulders arms
fuller length delivery outside off stump, Dilshan comes on the frontfoot and drives that to gully

good length delivery down the leg, Dilshan goes on the backfoot and turns it to square leg
too full on the stumps and its driven back down the ground, the ball ricochets off the stumps and deflects away for one towards mid-on
short of length delivery outside off, Dilshan goes on the backfoot and cuts it to point
full outside off stump, driven into the covers for one, the batsmen have to run quick as the fielders converge
fullish again, driven in the gap at mid-off down to long-off for an easy single

run out! A fullish ball on middle and leg is tucked past square leg, the batsmen take one and decide on the second, but Fulton in the deep is quick and fires in the throw to McGlashan, and Silva is just too slow coming back, there really was no second run on offer, and indecision is the culprit
good length, moving outside off stump, he stands and plays away from his body and gets beaten
fullish on middle and leg, Silva turns it to square leg
straighter on the stumps, and its worked into midwicket for a quick single
good length outside off stump, he goes back and opens the face, running it down to third man for one
a tad fuller outside off stump, and he drives loosely and gets beaten

banged in short outside off stump, and Malinga goes back and leaves it be
full and wide outside off stump, Malinga stands and plays away from his body, and he's nowhere near that one
good length on middle and leg, he looks to tuck it fine but doesnt time it well, getting an inside edge to the off side
full and wide outside off stump, he swings merrily and misses
strays down leg side, and its tucked around the corner to fine leg for one
full and wide outside off stump, he drives and misses, playing well away from his body

fuller length delivery on the stumps, Malinga looks to flick it away, inside edge onto the pads

full outside off stump, driven into the covers
good length on the stumps, defended back to Astle
a good length outside off stump, Malinga stands and pokes at it, and misses

good length outside off stump, Fernando backs away and tries to dab it to point, but ends up with an inside edge

fuller length delivery on the stumps, Fernando comes on the frontfoot and goes for the drive, inside edges it to fine leg

full outside the off stump, and thats a nice cover drive for one out to the sweeper
pitched up outside off stump, Fernando opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
good shot! Short of a length delivery outside off stump, Malinga goes on the backfoot and cuts it to square third man and he becomes the innings top-scorer
short of a length delivery on the stumps, Malinga goes on the backfoot and mistimes the pull to mid -wicket

whoah! Full outside off stump, Malinga gets under it and lofts it down to long-off, where the fielder jumps up on the ropes, gets the hands on it, but falls over the boundary in the  process, and though he threw the ball back on the green, the umpire decrees that some part of him was over the ropes, and signals six!
full toss on the stumps, Fernando comes on the frontfoot and drives it to mid wicket
delivery looped up on the off, Malinga comes on the frontfoot and drives it to cover
tossed up on the stumps, Fernando comes on the frontfoot and defends it
flat on middle and leg, driven to mid-wicket
flat outside off stump, down on one knee goes Fernando and swings it to square leg, calls for the run and McCullum at deep square leg fires in a low, flat throw but the run is taken
full outside off stump, and Fernado drives that well over mid-off for four more, what a partnership this is turning out to be!
full toss on middle and leg, Malinga comes on the frontfoot and drives it to long on
good length delivery down the leg, Fernando goes on the backfoot and flicks it to deep mid-wicket
another full toss on the middle and leg, Malinga launches forward and drives it to long on
fuller length delivery on the stumps, Fernando comes on the frontfoot and drives it to deep mid wicket, great placement
speared into the legs, the yorker, and it beats Fernando all ends up, but misses the stumps
all over! Full toss on the stumps, Fernando heaves it on the leg side, it goes high over the infield, but  lands smack in Adams's hands at the deep mid-wicket boundary
yorker length delivery on middle and leg, Malinga looks to drive, and misses
thats that! Tossed up on middle and leg, Malinga looks to slam that over the off side, misses, and the ball hits the top of leg stump!
good length outside off stump, McCullum pushes it into the covers
good ball! A lifter outside off stump, bounce and movement suckers McCullum up on his toes and then shaves past his bat, well bowled
shot! Quick, short and wide outside off stump, slightly cramped for room but McCullum is just too quick on it, and uppercuts it over point for four to get the innings going
short and wide again, McCullum backs away and flays the bat at it, but cant make contact this time
and again its just too short and wide outside off stump, but McCullum cant get bat to it even though he gave it the kitchen sink
good length outside off stump, McCullum gets up on his toes and pokes at it with an open face of the bat, gets the edge that flies wide of third slip, and picks up four as there was no third man
wide ball to start off with, pitches full and wide outside off stump and deviates too much
full and swinging away outside off stump, Fleming gets half forward and then leaves it alone

full on off stump, Fleming looks to work it into the on side but doesnt time it, and gets an inside edge towards Dilshan at point, McCullum calls for the run and just makes it as Dilshan's throw comes in
bang! Full and wide outside off stump, McCullum picks it up and slams it over mid-off off the backfoot for four
wide, way down the leg side
good length ball outside off stump, McCullum drives it to mid-off
full and wide outside off stump and McCullum gives it everything he has, leaning back, getting under it, and splicing it high over backward point for four

good length delivery on the stumps, Fleming comes on the front foot and plays it back to the bowler
full and moving down  leg stump, Fleming goes for the flick but doesnt time it, ends up clipping the pad and McCullum calls for the run and gets it
short and wide, 150ks, rising too but McCullum cant get bat onto it as he opts for a lavish uppercut
good length delivery outside the off stump, McCullum goes on the backfoot and slaps it to deep backward point
a bouncer is the reply! Well bowled! Quick on middle and leg, forces McCullum down onto his haunches as it sails over his left shoulder
half-volley outside off stump, and Fleming just slams that handsomely over mid-off for four, stand and swing shot that was
shorter outside off stump, Fleming looks to slap it over point, the ball hurries on him but he's timed it so well nevertheless that it sails over cover for four, innovation there!
fuller length delivery on the off, Fleming comes on the frontfoot and drives it to mid off
good length delivery angling into the left-hander, seaming away, Fleming looks to slam it over the leg side, but misses

good ball, lands outside off stump and swing over the top of the stumps, and Fleming suprisingly leaves it be, that was close but guess he's pretty confident of where his off stump is

short and wide, McCullum flays his bat at it but misses, and its called wide anyways
back of a length delivery outside off stump,McCullum opens the face of the bat and plays that to gully

gone! A good length delivery outside off stump and Fleming goes for an expansive drive, was a bit late on the shot, and ends up skies skying it over point and Kapugedera takes a well-judged catch out in the deep
short of a length delivery outside off stump, McCullum goes for the cut, misses

short of a length delivery outside off, McCullum goes on the backfoot and cuts it to point

flighted delivery on the stumps, Astle comes on the frontfoot and turns it to short mid-wicket
flatter on leg stump, Astle goes on back and glances it to short fine leg
another run out! Madness! Tossed up on middle and leg, Astle turns it to the onside, McCullum sets off down the track but Astle says no and New Zealand have anothe run-out mess on their hands
fuller length delivery on the off, Fulton comes on the frontfoot and drives it to cover
short of length delivery outside off, Fulton goes on the backfoot and pushes it to sweeper cover
flighted delivery down leg, Astle kneels down and sweeps it to fine leg
fuller length delivery on middle and leg, Fulton comes on the frontfoot and drives it to long-on
short of a length outside off stump, Astle goes for the cut and misses
tossed up down leg, Astle goes on the backfoot and turns it to square leg
flighted delivery on off stump, Astle comes on the frontfoot and plays it back to the bowler
flatter on leg stump, worked past square leg and they run well
flat on middle and leg, Fulton comes forward and drives past mid-on for one
flat again but on middle and off, Astle goes back and works it to mid-wicket
short and wide outside off, Astle goes on the backfoot and cuts it to deep backward point
flat down leg stump, he tries to work it fine but cant time it well&
tossed up on leg stump, Fulton drives to mid-on
shot! Tossed up on off stump, Fulton gets to the pitch of it and drives that straight down the ground past mid-off for four
flighted delivery outside off stump, Fulton reaches for it and punches it to the sweeper cover
tossed up on the stumps, Astle gets the foot out of the way and slams it, golf-like, between the nonstriker and the stumps for four, super shot
quicker through the air, pitches on off stump, Astle drives back to Bandara
short of a length delivery outside off stump, Astle goes on the backfoot and cuts it square for a brace
and bowls a good ball first up, pitches it outside off stump and gets it to stand up, Fulton plays a nothing shot and gets beaten

where did that come from?? Holy mackerel!! Banged in short on middle and leg, and Fulton swivels on one foot and hooks it superbly over deep backward square leg, and thats so far back it lands up in the balcony somewhere!
good length delivery on the stumps, Fulton shuffles across and tries to tap it away, ends up with an inside edge onto the pads
fuller outside off stump, Fulton comes forward and drives it straight down the ground, Fernando does well to get a finger to it and take the pace off it
short of a length delivery on the stumps, Fulton goes on the backfoot and looks to pull it away, misses and gets hit on the chest
gone! Full and swinging into him, Fulton doesnt pick it well and has an ugly swipe across the line, eyes not on the ball at all, and his stumps are re-arranged, Sri Lanka strike again!
tossed up on off stump, Astle defends back to Bandara
quicker outside off stump, Astle backs away and cuts it wide of point for one
looped up outside off stump, McGlashan comes forward and pushes to cover
flatter on middle and leg, he picks it up and flicks around the corner to short fine leg
short of a length delivery outside off, Astle goes on the backfoot and cuts it to point, straight to the fielder
flatter outside leg stump, he shuffles across and tries to flick it, ball clips the pads
good length on leg stump, worked off the hips wide of square leg
full and wide of off stump, he comes down the track and swings wildly at it and misses all ends up
shorter on off stump, Astle tries to pull but doesnt time it well, does get bat on it and it trickles past short fine leg

another one bites the dust! Simple catch! Banged in short outside off stump, McGlashan is taken by suprise and defends loosely on the hop, the ball takes the shoulder of the bat and loops up in the air, and all point has to do is take a few steps forward and accept the easiest of chances
short of a good length outside off stump, hurries into him but he plays it well withs soft hands to gully
full outside off stump, slower too, and Franklin drives to the offside loosely
full outside off stump, too much width, and its slow to boot, 126ks, and Astle slams it hard over mid-off four four
quicker and it moves in from outside off to tuck Astle up, but he does well to work it to square leg
strives for the yorker on leg stump, Franklin drives to mid-on
full and wide outside off stump, Astle has an ugly swing at that and fails to make contact...zip, zero, nada, nothing....
banged in short again, again he has a swipe and gets bat onto it, but can only chop into the ground for Perera to collect in his followthrough, but even he cant take it and gives up a run...ho ho ho
fuller length delivery on the stumps, Franklin comes on the front foot and turns it to short mid-wicket
full outside off stump, Astle makes room and drives expansively, but cant beat mid-off
good length on leg stump, an eager-beaver Astle swings at it and bottom-edges into the square leg region
short outside off stump, Franklin chops to cover, they set off, Atapattu is slow and cant get the pick-and-throw in time, and a sluggish Astle is home clear

thats the four he's been eyeing! Slow and full on the stumps, Astle moves his front leg out of the way and slams it bang smack down the ground, a couple bounces and over the ropes, pressure relieved now
whats the reply? A bouncer! Quick on middle and leg, forces Astle down onto his haunches
full on middle and leg, Impetuous Astle swipes across the line and mistimes it out to a wide mid-on, agricultural farming type of batting this...Twenty20 on Boxing Day, would you believe it?
hoo hah! The lengths all wrong for his chap, drops it short outside off stump and Astle picks it from where it lands and smokes it over mid-on for four, sweet!
fuller length delivery on the off, Astle goes for the booming drive, but gets the outside edge down to third man, great effort by Atapattu saves two runs
short and wide outside off stump, Astle's cramped for room but carries through with the back-foot slam, and luckily for him it goes over mid-off and lands safely
fuller length delivery on off stump, Franklin comes on the frontfoot and drives it to extra cover
bye bye birdie! Insane hit that! Full outside off stump, and Astle picks it so well, just sends it sailing miles and miles over wide long-on, thats so far back into the stands, wow, wow, wow!
slower and fuller outside off stump, Astle looks to square drive it but doesnt time it well, the ball bobs up and drops outside off stump, McGlashan calls for the mad single, and the scores are tied!
tossed up outside off stump, he drives but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket
tossed up outside leg, he tries to loft it for four but doesnt make contact
all over! Tossed up on middle and leg, Astle gets down and sweeps through square leg for one, and New Zealand have tied the series!
